Author: AlekseiKrivo
Message:
Fix for #3931 (normalScrollElements option)

There is a fix for the issue #3931, that appears when "normalScrollElements" option is added and mouse cursor leaves from a browser window.

When the mouse cursor left the viewport, the "scrollable" variable was not assigned a value, because the "target" parameter, in this case, is null. So, I just added a check for the "target" parameter value in 2409 line.

Merge pull request #3832 from jbez/dev

Reassigning value for isWindowFocused on focus event

Author: jbez
Message:
Setting isWindowFocused back to true after focus events.

Currently, isWindowFocused is set to true once on initialise(), then either forever true, or changed to false on blur events via the blurHandler(). Having triggered one blur, this is never set back to true upon any kind of focus event triggering on the window.
This, in turn, causes the keyUpHandler to never assign the variable controlPressed back to its original state of false, causing scrolling to not work, due to the MouseWheelHandler checking for !controlPressed.

This commit adds a focusHandler and adds it via window.addEventListener so isWindowFocused gets set to true again.
